rComments: Nigel is THE WORST PROFESSOR I've ever met. Unfortunately, his teaching is some of the worst I've encountered. AND his comments on the assignment are vague and unthoughtful. He keeps reiterating the same concept so that we do not have time for learning the rest of the material. AVOID AT ALL COSTS. I have to delay my graduation because of HIM!!!

Nigel is one of the nicest people I've ever met. Unfortunately, his teaching is some of the worst I've encountered. Lecture are super hard to follow, and he is the CEO of "oh, wait I forgot to tell you X..." so it's tough to take good notes for his class. He did give us hie own notes for the readings, though, which were really helpful.

Awesome teacher! I'm not even a philosophy student and I've done pretty great in it, but I feel like Nigel is a big part of why that's the case. He makes some of the dry content interesting and really gives off great vibes as a whole. Was a bit spooked about the course but gave me the confidence to stick with it and I'm glad I did.

DESOUZA IS THE BEST. Hands down the best professor. He cares about his students LEARNING, he's reasonable about different levels of obligations (if you're managing a job ect) which helps eliminate the elitism of academics. He's passionate, intelligent, articulate, and incredibly kind. I try to take at least one course with him a year <3

I had difficulty understanding how to get a good grade, and when I approached him I was told to "be realistic" but other than that I felt that Professor Desouza was a good professor. He knew his stuff, and was clearly passionate which made the class more enjoyable.

DeSouza is awesome! He clearly cares about his students and wants to see them succeed. He is very passionate about the material he teaches and it gives him great joy when students engage with it in a genuine way. The readings he assigns are by no means a walk in the park but he is such a skilled communicator and does a great job of explaining them

Amazing, amazing prof. One of the few to care about his students. Great interactivity. ATTEND LECTURES, if you take good notes, you will finish the class with an A as he stresses the main points that will be on the exam. Highly recommended.
He is one of the BEST PROFESSORS I have ever had in my life. He speaks very well, BILINGUAL!!! And CARES alot about his students. The exams are fair and he guides your studying. Thank you so much!!

This prof is amazing. He is extremely kind and willing to help his students. He does everything in his power to help his students understand the material. For both the midterm and the final, practice questions were provided. The lectures are important as you are tested only on what is spoken in class. I would love to take a class with Desouza again

Super caring prof, really cares about the students and encourages participation. The TAs can mark tough, but he's great at explaining all the concepts. Attend the lectures so you know what the key points are from each article and try to keep up with them every week. Essay topics were good, midterm was very fair, and final was good! Lots of writing.

Clearly cares about the students and the material he's teaching. He aims to help you as much as he can within reason. He tends to over explain material, but that's better than under explaining so I'll gladly take it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Probably the kindest, most caring prof I've ever had. Lectures can be a little long but interesting.
Amazing prof, took a really hard philosophy class with him and he somehow made it  much easier and interesting! Definitely recommend.

One of the best profs I've had in philosophy! He cares so much about his students and you can really tell he's passionate about what he teaches, would definitely recommend to any student in philosophy.
Incredibly kind professor.
One of the best teachers at the University. Take notes of what he says in class and it's an easy A.
Great. Too good. Very good. Incredible. Not bad. Fun. Okay. Meh... Likes to talk. Likes to present. Likes to lecture. Likes to listen. Likes food. Hates laptops.

best prof ever omg.. he's extremely nice, helpful, remembers who you are in the class and is a really good teacher.. he's super clear in his expectations and in his lectures. He makes philosophy really interesting and really pulls you into the discussion... i even had a telfer friend sit in on his class and she loved his lecture!

Professor DeSouza was a great professor! He made every lecture interesting and was very good to tell you steps to improve scores. As long as you read the articles and attend class you should have no problem getting a good grade. Would definitely take again!

Phenomenal professor and phenomenal guy. Go to office hours. Not only will you learn new things but you'll also make a new friend. Easily my favourite professor. Also, my TA was not only attractive, but extremely helpful, AND incredibly hilarious. Shout-out to Liepens!

Professor DeSouza is the best professor I have EVER had at UOttawa. This guy's teaching style is amazing, and he explains the info in a way that you can easily understand. Expectations are super clear. You can tell he is legitimately excited about the course material. By far my favorite professor. Well done, Professor DeSouza.

By far one of the best profs I had my first year at UO. He types up all of the notes in class so the expectations of the readings couldn't be more clear.  He gives you the Q's to the exams beforehand so you can prepare the exact answer you will write in your exam. Seriously, take this course... I guarantee you won't regret it.

Desouza is one of the best professor's at this university. He is funny and a tad bit quirky, but really cares for the subjects and his students. He makes an effort to make a personal connection with as many students as he can, and loves class discussions. I would definitely take a class of his again and recommend him to anyone who is in philosophy.

This was one of the easiest classes I had first year because of this prof. Completely unnecessary to do the readings because his lectures were solely about the readings. He did an amazing job of summarizing and explaining the material. And all the readings were online so no textbook purchased! TAKE HIS CLASS.

Very kind, writes his notes and summaries of the articles on the projector for everyone, so you just need to read the articles. No textbook to buy. Gives all the midterm and exam questions ahead of time so you can preparr. Interesting and controversial topics and he encourages group discussions. Great prof.

The nicest professor I've had at UOttawa. He is always open to discussion with students. The material is abstract and hard to grasp, but he does the best job of trying to keep interesting. Plus, he gives exam questions to you ahead, so it's super easy to do well. Always makes sure the students can understand what h he is trying to explain.

Phenomenal class. Nigel is a great guy and an even better teacher. EXTREMELY helpful in office hours. Some might find it boring, but if you like philosophy, you will love this class. He gives you midterm and exam questions beforehand. If you pay attention in class and follow the textbook you WILL do well in this class. Best professor hands down!!

Very sweet professor. He really wants all his students to do well, gives you the questions before the midterm and exam and is very helpful if you approach him. Always repeats things that are misunderstood in class. A real nice guy :) I'd definitely take another class with him.

Best, funniest philosophy prof for mandatory philosophy classes. He makes the material as easy as possible because he knows that many people are forced to take the course. He gave us the questions for the midterms and exams, and he teaches right out of the book. He does write on the chalkboard but it fits really well with his teaching style.
Could't understand what he was talking about most of the time.  Wrote on the blackboard for the entire class and said what he wrote out loud...

amazing prof, favourite over many years! very helpful (responds to emails quickly, great with office hours), and really puts the effort to make the subject understandable to the class. Philosophy tends to be mandatory, I suggest making a point of ensuring you get him as a prof!

I had no complaints with this class. Easy class chill professor. Just do the readings, and you should have no problem getting at least an A-. Also, there is no textbook, just online articles. We just had 2 midterms (25% each) and the final was 50%. He gave us the answers prior to the first, the second was open book, and the final was take-home! (y)
realllllllly boring course. The prof wrote on the chalkboard for the entire class! His notes were pretty confusing. At least he had exam preparation questions though.
